12/04/2006
LUXEMBOURG -- Romanian Foreign Minister Mihai Razvan Ungureanu said in Luxembourg Tuesday (11 April) that Romania and Bulgaria might jointly ask the EU to issue a clear statement on the two countries' accession date.
He says he and Bulgarian counterpart Ivailo Kalfin recently discussed the matter, in hopes a special declaration concerning the date is issued during the EU Ministerial Council summit in June.
In other news, EU Environmental Commissioner Stavros Dimas, who visited Bucharest on Tuesday, called on Romania to work harder to meet its environmental protection obligations related to EU membership.
Dimas acknowledged, however, that Romania has achieved considerable process in the area.
(Nine o'clock - 12/04/06;
Reuters - 11/04/06)
